{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"patch":0,"major":0},"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/childwatchsourcenew(pid:)"]}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/childWatchSourceNew(pid:)"},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"childWatchSourceNew","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"pid"},{"kind":"text","text":": "},{"text":"GPid","preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GPid","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":") -> ","kind":"text"},{"text":"SourceRef","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib9SourceRefV","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/SourceRef","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"!"}],"platforms":["macOS"],"languages":["swift"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"content":[{"level":2,"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The source will not initially be associated with any","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[struct"},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext"},{"text":"] and must be added to one with","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"[method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.Source.attach"},{"text":"] before it will be executed.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that child watch sources can only be used in conjunction with"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"g_spawn..."},{"text":" when the [flags","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.SpawnFlags.DO_NOT_REAP_CHILD"},{"text":"] flag is used.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Note that on platforms where [type"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Pid","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":"] must be explicitly closed"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"(see [func"},{"code":"GLib.spawn_close_pid","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"]) ","type":"text"},{"code":"pid","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" must not be closed while the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"source is still active. Typically, you will want to call"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"[func"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.spawn_close_pid"},{"text":"] in the callback function for the source.","type":"text"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"On POSIX platforms, the following restrictions apply to this API","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"due to limitations in POSIX process interfaces:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"unorderedList","items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pid"},{"type":"text","text":" must be a child of this process."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pid"},{"text":" must be positive.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The application must not call ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"man:waitpid(1)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" with a","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"non-positive first argument, for instance in another thread."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The application must not wait for "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pid"},{"text":" to exit by any other","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"mechanism, including "},{"code":"waitpid(pid, ...)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" or a second child-watch","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"source for the same "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"pid"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The application must not ignore "},{"code":"SIGCHLD","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Before 2.78, the application could not send a signal ("},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"man:kill(2)"},{"text":") to the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"watched ","type":"text"},{"code":"pid","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in a race free manner. Since 2.78, you can do that while the","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"associated [struct"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/MainContext","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":"] is acquired.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Before 2.78, even after destroying the [struct"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Source","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"], you could not"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"be sure that ","type":"text"},{"code":"pid","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" wasn’t already reaped. Hence, it was also not","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"safe to ","type":"text"},{"code":"kill()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"waitpid()"},{"text":" on the process ID after the child watch","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"source was gone. Destroying the source before it fired made it"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"impossible to reliably reap the process."}]}]}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"If any of those conditions are not met, this and related APIs will","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"not work correctly. This can often be diagnosed via a GLib warning"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"stating that ","type":"text"},{"code":"ECHILD","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" was received by ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"waitpid()"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Calling ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"man:waitpid(2)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" for specific processes other than ","type":"text"},{"code":"pid","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"remains a valid thing to do.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Function","externalID":"s:4GLib19childWatchSourceNew3pidAA0D3RefVSgs5Int32V_tF","fragments":[{"text":"func","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"childWatchSourceNew","kind":"identifier"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"externalParam","text":"pid"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"c:@T@GPid","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"GPid"},{"kind":"text","text":") -> "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib9SourceRefV","text":"SourceRef"},{"text":"!","kind":"text"}],"role":"symbol","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"symbolKind":"func","title":"childWatchSourceNew(pid:)"},"abstract":[{"text":"Creates a new child watch source.","type":"text"}],"references":{"man:waitpid(1)":{"url":"man:waitpid(1)","type":"link","identifier":"man:waitpid(1)","titleInlineContent":[{"code":"waitpid()","type":"codeVoice"}],"title":"waitpid()"},"man:kill(2)":{"title":"kill()","type":"link","identifier":"man:kill(2)","titleInlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"kill()"}],"url":"man:kill(2)"},"man:waitpid(2)":{"title":"waitpid()","type":"link","identifier":"man:waitpid(2)","titleInlineContent":[{"code":"waitpid()","type":"codeVoice"}],"url":"man:waitpid(2)"},"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/Pid":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/Pid","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/glib\/pid","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"typealias"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Pid","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"